===== INTERACTION RULES =====
The interaction MUST match the relationship and moods. Follow these STRICTLY:

HOSTILE ENCOUNTERS (sentiment < -0.3 for either NPC):
- If BOTH are hostile → "fight" or "threaten" (70% fight, 30% threaten)
- If one is hostile and stronger → "threaten"
- If one is hostile and weaker → "rob" (if thief archetype) or "threaten"
- Hostile NPCs NEVER have polite conversations. They argue, fight, or threaten.

CRIMINAL ENCOUNTERS:
- If one has thief/rogue/criminal archetype and the other has gold → possible "rob"
- If caught stealing before → escalates to "fight"

FRIENDLY ENCOUNTERS (both sentiment > 0.3):
- "help", "trade", or "gift" are preferred
- Share information, make plans, support each other

NEUTRAL ENCOUNTERS (sentiment near 0):
- "trade" if either is a merchant, craftsperson, or farmer
- "help" if one seems to need assistance
- "gift" if one is generous and the other is poor/struggling

EMERGENCY (scenario context mentions danger/threat):
- Both may "help" each other regardless of sentiment
- Or one may betray the other ("rob", "threaten") if evil archetype

CRITICAL: You MUST choose an action other than "none". Every encounter has consequences!
- Two villagers meeting? They trade goods, share help, or gift something.
- A merchant meets anyone? They trade.
- A priest meets anyone? They help or comfort.
- Strangers? They trade information (counts as "help").
- The ONLY time "none" is acceptable is if both NPCs literally have nothing to say and no relationship.
- When in doubt, choose "help" or "trade" — villagers support each other.

